<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-19T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-19T05:00:00-05:00" n="553" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d553">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">894.5151/155: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-19T19:00:00+09:00">August 19, 1939—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 19—8:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>418. Our 404, August 12, 2 p.m.<note n="33" xml:id="d553fn33">Not
                                    printed.</note> Foreign Office advised us informally today that
                                Ministry of Finance will hereafter issue permits regularly with a
                                time lag of 2 months: permit for June remittance to be issued in
                                September, July remittance in October and so on. Foreign Office
                                added that this will be communicated to us formally by note early
                                next week.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dooman</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>